<div id="banner">
	<h1>Donald Knuth writes Condi Rice</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p><a href="http://www-cs-faculty.stanford.edu/~knuth/rice.html">Knuth: Open Letter to Condolezza Rice</a></p>

<blockquote>
  <p>When I knew you at Stanford I had the greatest admiration for your abilities and good sense. (And I was disappointed that we never were able to get together to play four-hands music.) But now I cannot help but express to you my chagrin that the warm feelings I once had have basically evaporated. I hope you can pause to try to understand why this might be the case.</p>
</blockquote>

<p><em>Donald Knuth is the widely-respected author of the classic series</em> The Art of Computer Programming. <em>Condolezza Rice is the National Security Advisor to President Bush.</em></p>

<p class="posted">posted November 08, 2004 08:15 PM (<a class="category" href="cat_politics">Politics</a>) (<a href="#comments">8 comments</a>) <a href="001469" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

